accessibility.text: While ideally we would want our code coverage to be at 100% in all metrics, it becomes realistically infeasible as the program expands to a large scale.
While ideally we would want our code coverage to be at 100% in all metrics, it becomes realistically infeasible as the program expands to a large scale.
There isn’t a universal threshold on how much coverage is constituted as “good”. Most major code projects aim to reach 60-80% line/branch coverage and 100% of function coverage.
Having higher code coverage often requires  higher financial and time costs, which can be  diverted to other parts of the project.
